<a class="bookmark" title="outlook" name="outlook"></a>
<h2>Adding an Email Signature to Outlook</h2>
<ol>
	<li>Open a new message. </li>
	<li>On the Message tab, in the Include group, click <em>Signature</em>, and then click <em>Signatures</em>. <br/><br/><img src="/uploadedImages/Content/Prevention_and_Preparedness/immunize/niam/2016/outlook-include-signature.png" alt="Screen capture of Include Group with Signature item highlighted" title="Screen capture of Include Group with Signature item highlighted"/><br/><br/></li>
	<li>On the <em>E-mail Signature</em> tab, click <em>New</em>.<br/><br/><img src="/uploadedImages/Content/Prevention_and_Preparedness/immunize/niam/2016/outlook-new-signature.png" alt="Screen capture of Email Signature tab with New button highlighted" title="Screen capture of Email Signature tab with New button highlighted"/><br/><br/></li>
	<li>Type a name for the signature, and then click <em>OK</em>.<br/><br/><img src="/uploadedImages/Content/Prevention_and_Preparedness/immunize/niam/2016/outlook-signature-name.jpg" alt="Screen capture of adding a new signature name in Outlook" title="Screen capture of adding a new signature name in Outlook"/><br/><br/></li>
	<li>Copy and paste the following image into the editor:<br/><br/><a href="http://www.dshs.state.tx.us/immunize/NIAM/2016/" title="August 2016 is National Immunization Awareness Month"><img src="http://heaven-chef.codio.io:3000/immunize/NIAM/2016/img/niam-logo-sm.jpg" style="" alt="August 2016 is National Immunization Awareness Month" /></a><br/><br/></li>
	<li>Click <em>OK</em> to close the window.</li>
</ol>

<hr/>
<a class="bookmark" title="ios" name="ios"></a>
<h2>Adding an Email Signature to iOS (iPhone / iPad)</h2>
<ol>
	<li>On a desktop or laptop computer, copy and paste the following image and link into an email that you send to yourself:<br/><br/><img src="/uploadedImages/Content/Prevention_and_Preparedness/immunize/niam/2016/niam-logo-sm.jpg" style="" alt="August 2016 is National Immunization Awareness Month" /><br/><a title="http://www.dshs.state.tx.us/immunize/NIIW/2016/" href="/immunize/NIAM/2016/">http://www.dshs.state.tx.us/immunize/NIIW/2016/</a><br/><br/></li>	
	<li>Open the email in your iOS device. Press and hold on a part of message until the context menu appears.<br/><br/><img src="/uploadedImages/Content/Prevention_and_Preparedness/immunize/niam/2016/ios-select-signature.png" alt="Screen capture showing selection of email signature content" title="Screen capture showing selection of email signature content"/><br/><br/></li>
	<li>From the context menu, choose <em>Select All</em> and then <em>Copy</em>.</li>
	<li>Open <em>Settings</em> on the iPhone/iPad Home screen.</li>
	<li>Go to <em>Mail</em> &gt; <em>Contacts</em> &gt; <em>Calendars</em>.</li>
	<li>Tap <em>Signature</em> under <em>Mail</em>.</li>
	<li>To set up one signature for all your email accounts make sure <em>All Accounts</em> is selected.</li>
	<li>To have iOS Mail use signatures specific to accounts make sure <em>Per Account</em> is selected.</li>
	<li>Paste the picture from the email into the signature block.</li>
</ol>

